external_knowledge:
- Precision and recall are performance metrics used in machine learning to evaluate the effectiveness of a model;
- A higher precision indicates a model that produces fewer false positives;
- Collaborators are users who contribute to the development or annotation of a model.

- "model type" refers to the category or kind of machine learning model, such as classification or regression;
- "average precision" is a metric used to evaluate the performance of a model, where a higher value indicates better performance;
- "stands tallest" is a metaphorical expression meaning the model type with the highest average precision.

- 'classification' refers to machine learning models used to predict categorical labels;
- 'F-measure' is a metric that combines precision and recall, providing a balanced measure of a model's performance;
- 'version changes' indicate the number of times a model has been updated or modified.

- 'Shining stars' refers to the models with the highest average F-measure;
- 'Leading the pack' means ranking first in their category;
- 'Classification models' are models with the type 'classification'.

- 'blossomed in their first version' refers to models with version number '1.0';
- 'part of the garden of project 1' refers to models associated with project ID 1;
- 'put to the test of evaluation' refers to models that have tasks of type 'evaluation'.

- "blossomed with the wisdom of multiple minds" refers to models with more than one collaborator;
- "judged in more than one report" means the models have been evaluated in more than one report;
- "precision and recall scores exceeding 80%" refers to precision > 0.8 and recall > 0.8;
- "with the most collaborative ones leading the way" means the results are ordered by the number of collaborators in descending order.

- 'First version' refers to models with a version number of '1.0';
- 'Start of the new year' refers to January 1, 2023;
- 'Higher-than-average precision' means the average precision of the model is greater than the average precision of all models evaluated after December 31, 2022.

- "latest notes" refers to the most recent annotation text for each model;
- "most recent hyperparameters" are the latest hyperparameter entries for each model;
- "evaluation metrics" refer to the latest evaluation dates for each model.

- "shining star" refers to the model with the highest average F-measure, precision, and recall;
- "garden of machine learning" represents the collection of models in the database;
- "well-visited" indicates high total evaluations and downloads.

